<body>
<segment id="1" parent="1001" relname="preparation">Handle</segment>
<segment id="2" parent="1002" relname="preparation">Differences of Opinion</segment>
<segment id="3" parent="1004" relname="concession">An opinion is not fact ,</segment>
<segment id="4" parent="1004" relname="contrast">but what someone thinks</segment>
<segment id="5" parent="1004" relname="contrast">or believes .</segment>
<segment id="6" parent="1007" relname="joint">Not everyone will have the same opinions on things ,</segment>
<segment id="7" parent="1007" relname="joint">and some opinions are very hard to change .</segment>
<segment id="8" parent="1009" relname="circumstance">Since people think different ,</segment>
<segment id="9" parent="1009" relname="span">try these steps</segment>
<segment id="10" parent="1010" relname="joint">to reduce differences</segment>
<segment id="11" parent="1010" relname="joint">and see what happens .</segment>
<segment id="12" parent="1012" relname="preparation">Steps</segment>
<segment id="13" parent="1014" relname="preparation">Try to think like the other person .</segment>
<segment id="14" parent="1016" relname="concession">Sometimes , it seems hard to look at something from another perspective ,</segment>
<segment id="15" parent="1016" relname="span">but it &apos;s a good way</segment>
<segment id="16" parent="1018" relname="attribution">to understand</segment>
<segment id="17" parent="1018" relname="span">why they feel</segment>
<segment id="18" parent="17" relname="circumstance">as they do .</segment>
<segment id="19" parent="1020" relname="same_unit">You see ,</segment>
<segment id="20" parent="21" relname="condition">if you really try to understand both sides ,</segment>
<segment id="21" parent="1021" relname="span">you can approach the issue more neutrally .</segment>
<segment id="22" parent="23" relname="concession">Religion and love can be very debatable ,</segment>
<segment id="23" parent="1023" relname="span">but that &apos;s not the point .</segment>
<segment id="24" parent="1025" relname="span">You can understand someone</segment>
<segment id="25" parent="24" relname="condition">if you really want to get along with them .</segment>
<segment id="26" parent="1026" relname="joint">This is not about RIGHT versus WRONG .</segment>
<segment id="27" parent="1028" relname="preparation">Consider the following examples :</segment>
<segment id="28" parent="1030" relname="condition">If you &apos;re with same sex marriage ,</segment>
<segment id="29" parent="30" relname="attribution">try to understand</segment>
<segment id="30" parent="1030" relname="span">why someone else might not approve of those of the same gender marrying .</segment>
<segment id="31" parent="1032" relname="span">It does go against some religious rules</segment>
<segment id="32" parent="31" relname="elaboration">held by some people .</segment>
<segment id="33" parent="1036" relname="condition">If you are opposed to same sex marriage ,</segment>
<segment id="34" parent="1036" relname="span">try to put yourself in a position</segment>
<segment id="35" parent="1037" relname="contrast">where you love someone very much ,</segment>
<segment id="36" parent="1038" relname="span">but you ca n&apos;t get married</segment>
<segment id="37" parent="36" relname="cause">because other people have an issue with it .</segment>
<segment id="38" parent="1040" relname="contrast">Suppose your child wants to go on a vacation with a friend ,</segment>
<segment id="39" parent="1040" relname="contrast">but there could problems and implications without his/her guardian with them on the trip .</segment>
<segment id="40" parent="1043" relname="circumstance">As the parent ,</segment>
<segment id="41" parent="1044" relname="attribution">try to understand</segment>
<segment id="42" parent="1044" relname="joint">why your child wants to go and have fun ,</segment>
<segment id="43" parent="1045" relname="span">and why being denied permission seems unfair</segment>
<segment id="44" parent="1046" relname="span">simply</segment>
<segment id="45" parent="1047" relname="joint">because you &apos;re working the weekend</segment>
<segment id="46" parent="1048" relname="span">and he/she will be left with nothing</segment>
<segment id="47" parent="46" relname="purpose">to do .</segment>
<segment id="48" parent="1050" relname="span">Your mom has refused to let you go on a trip with your friend .</segment>
<segment id="49" parent="1052" relname="joint">Try to put yourself in her shoes</segment>
<segment id="50" parent="1054" relname="attribution">and you &apos;ll realize</segment>
<segment id="51" parent="1055" relname="preparation">your mother is going to worry about you ;</segment>
<segment id="52" parent="1055" relname="span">there &apos;s no way</segment>
<segment id="53" parent="52" relname="purpose">to stop her from it .</segment>
<segment id="54" parent="1056" relname="span">To her , your safety is more important</segment>
<segment id="55" parent="54" relname="antithesis">than how much fun you could have with your friend .</segment>
<segment id="56" parent="1058" relname="joint">Give it time</segment>
<segment id="57" parent="1058" relname="joint">and see if the argument will fade away .</segment>
<segment id="58" parent="1060" relname="joint">You and your friend have a fight about something ,</segment>
<segment id="59" parent="1061" relname="span">and there is no possible way</segment>
<segment id="60" parent="59" relname="elaboration">you will agree on it - ever .</segment>
<segment id="61" parent="1063" relname="sequence">Step away</segment>
<segment id="62" parent="1064" relname="span">and give yourself time</segment>
<segment id="63" parent="62" relname="purpose">to think about it .</segment>
<segment id="64" parent="65" relname="condition">If you really care about someone ,</segment>
<segment id="65" parent="1066" relname="span">you can set every difference aside</segment>
<segment id="66" parent="1065" relname="joint">and still be their friend .</segment>
<segment id="67" parent="1069" relname="span">You can always try to make them understand</segment>
<segment id="68" parent="67" relname="elaboration">( in a calm way )</segment>
<segment id="69" parent="1071" relname="attribution">that you understand</segment>
<segment id="70" parent="1071" relname="joint">why he/she wo n&apos;t change their mind</segment>
<segment id="71" parent="1071" relname="joint">and why you wo n&apos;t either .</segment>
<segment id="72" parent="1072" relname="joint">Explain that you should just let it go</segment>
<segment id="73" parent="1073" relname="joint">and set it aside</segment>
<segment id="74" parent="1073" relname="joint">because , in all honesty , your friendship is about much more than your differences .</segment>
<segment id="75" parent="1075" relname="preparation">Warnings</segment>
<segment id="76" parent="77" relname="condition">If talking to the person about the differences ,</segment>
<segment id="77" parent="1076" relname="span">do n&apos;t be rude .</segment>
<segment id="78" parent="1077" relname="span">Come to your friend calmly and rationally ,</segment>
<segment id="79" parent="78" relname="cause">because nobody likes someone with a rude attitude .</segment>
